main event: A P-40 aircraft at 43,000 feet altitude observed an unidentified object over Volos, Greece at around 15,000 feet.
interesting points: The object veered to the MEB then disappeared rearward.
The pilot estimated the speed of the object to be between 600-700 knots.
The Centralis radar station did not track the object, despite the pilot informing them of the sighting.
The report includes analysis of the sighting, including consideration of potential astronomical phenomena and radar data.
The sighting appears to have been evaluated, but the conclusions are not provided in the text shown.
